vars: {
  d2-config: {
    layout-engine: elk
    theme-id: 4
  }
}

direction: down

title: |'md
## `sha256_update()` Three-Phase Buffer Management
Data Flow: Arbitrary chunk bytes -> SHA-256 block stream
'|
title.near: top-center

entry: |md
**ENTRY**
`sha256_update(ctx, data, len)`
| {
  style.fill: "#E8D5F5"
  style.stroke: "#7B2D8B"
  style.border-radius: 6
  style.font-size: 13
}

accum: |md
**Step 0 — Accumulate bit count**
`ctx->total_bits += (uint64_t)len * 8`
*(must happen before any early return)*
| {
  style.fill: "#D6EAF8"
  style.stroke: "#2874A6"
  style.border-radius: 6
  style.font-size: 13
}

entry -> accum: "all paths"

phase1_check: "`ctx->buf_len > 0` ?" {
  shape: diamond
  style.fill: "#FEF9E7"
  style.stroke: "#B7950B"
  style.font-size: 13
}

accum -> phase1_check

phase1_calc: |md
**Phase 1 — Fill existing buffer**
`need    = 64 - ctx->buf_len`
`can_use = min(len, need)`
`memcpy(ctx->buf + buf_len, data, can_use)`
`ctx->buf_len += can_use`
`i = can_use`
| {
  style.fill: "#FDF2E9"
  style.stroke: "#CA6F1E"
  style.border-radius: 6
  style.font-size: 13
}

phase1_check -> phase1_calc: "YES\n(bytes already buffered)"
phase1_check -> phase2_loop: "NO\n(buffer empty)\ni = 0" {
  style.stroke-dash: 4
}

phase1_full_check: "`ctx->buf_len == 64` ?" {
  shape: diamond
  style.fill: "#FEF9E7"
  style.stroke: "#B7950B"
  style.font-size: 13
}

phase1_calc -> phase1_full_check

phase1_compress: |md
**Compress buffered block**
`sha256_compress(ctx->H, ctx->buf)`
`ctx->buf_len = 0`
*(buf content now stale - buf_len is the*
*authoritative "no valid data" signal)*
| {
  style.fill: "#FDEDEC"
  style.stroke: "#CB4335"
  style.border-radius: 6
  style.font-size: 13
}

phase1_full_check -> phase1_compress: "YES\n(buffer just filled)"

phase1_return: |md
**RETURN EARLY**
*(all len bytes consumed into buf;*
*no complete block yet)*
`ctx->buf_len` in [1, 63]
| {
  style.fill: "#EBF5FB"
  style.stroke: "#2E86C1"
  style.border-radius: 6
  style.font-size: 13
}

phase1_full_check -> phase1_return: "NO\n(buf partially filled)\nbuf_len < 64" {
  style.stroke-dash: 4
}

phase2_loop: "`i + 64 <= len` ?" {
  shape: diamond
  style.fill: "#FEF9E7"
  style.stroke: "#B7950B"
  style.font-size: 13
}

phase1_compress -> phase2_loop: "continue\n(i bytes consumed so far)"

phase2_compress: |md
**Phase 2 — Zero-copy block compression**
`sha256_compress(ctx->H, data + i)`
`i += 64`
*(passes pointer directly - no memcpy into buf)*
*(hot path for large inputs)*
| {
  style.fill: "#FDEDEC"
  style.stroke: "#CB4335"
  style.border-radius: 6
  style.font-size: 13
}

phase2_loop -> phase2_compress: "YES\n(>= 64 bytes remain)"
phase2_compress -> phase2_loop: "loop back\n(advance i by 64)"

phase3_check: "`len - i > 0` ?" {
  shape: diamond
  style.fill: "#FEF9E7"
  style.stroke: "#B7950B"
  style.font-size: 13
}

phase2_loop -> phase3_check: "NO\n(< 64 bytes remain)"

phase3_buffer: |md
**Phase 3 — Buffer tail bytes**
`remaining = len - i`
`memcpy(ctx->buf, data + i, remaining)`
`ctx->buf_len = remaining`
*(0 ... 63 bytes buffered)*
| {
  style.fill: "#FDF2E9"
  style.stroke: "#CA6F1E"
  style.border-radius: 6
  style.font-size: 13
}

phase3_check -> phase3_buffer: "YES\n(1 ... 63 bytes remain)"

phase3_skip: |md
*(no tail bytes -*
*buf already flushed)*
`ctx->buf_len = 0`
| {
  style.fill: "#EBF5FB"
  style.stroke: "#2E86C1"
  style.border-radius: 6
  style.font-size: 13
  style.opacity: 0.85
}

phase3_check -> phase3_skip: "NO\n(data was block-aligned)"

exit: |md
**EXIT**
Invariants restored:
`ctx->buf_len` in [0, 63]
`ctx->total_bits` = total Σ bits
| {
  style.fill: "#E8D5F5"
  style.stroke: "#7B2D8B"
  style.border-radius: 6
  style.font-size: 13
}

phase3_buffer -> exit
phase3_skip -> exit
phase1_return -> exit

worked_eg: |md
**Worked Example:**
`ctx->buf_len = 10` on entry, `len = 100`
Step 0: `total_bits += 800`
Phase 1: `need=54, fill buf -> buf_len=64`
         `-> compress, buf_len=0, i=54`
Phase 2: `54+64=118 > 100 -> skip loop`
Phase 3: `rem = 46 -> ctx->buf_len=46`
| {
  near: bottom-right
  style.fill: "#F4F6F7"
  style.stroke: "#7F8C8D"
  style.border-radius: 6
  style.font-size: 12
  style.italic: true
}

pointer_note: |'md
**Data pointer advancement**

data: `[--- 54 ---|--- 0 complete blocks ---|--- 46 ---]`
        Phase 1                             Phase 3
        i=0->54                             i=54->100

For `len=200`, `buf_len=0` entry:

data: `[--- 64 ---|--- 64 ---|--- 64 ---|--- 8 ---]`
        block 0     block 1     block 2    Phase 3
'|
pointer_note.near: bottom-left
pointer_note.style.fill: "#F4F6F7"
pointer_note.style.stroke: "#7F8C8D"
pointer_note.style.border-radius: 6
pointer_note.style.font-size: 12